content.html: ❮ PHP Array Reference

content.code_html:
<?php
$cars=array("Volvo","BMW","Toyota");
echo "I like " . $cars[0] . ", " . $cars[1] . " and " . $cars[2] . ".";
?>

content.text: The array() function is used to create an array.
content.html: The array() function is used to create an array.

content.text: In PHP, there are three types of arrays:
content.html: In PHP, there are three types of arrays:

content.code_html: array(value1, value2, value3, etc.)

Parameter Description
key Specifies the key (numeric or string)
value Specifies the value

<?php
$age=array("Peter"=>"35","Ben"=>"37","Joe"=>"43");
echo "Peter is " . $age['Peter'] . " years old.";
?>

<?php
$cars=array("Volvo","BMW","Toyota");
$arrlength=count($cars);

for($x=0;$x<$arrlength;$x++)
  {
  echo $cars[$x];
  echo "<br>";
  }
?>

<?php
$age=array("Peter"=>"35","Ben"=>"37","Joe"=>"43");

foreach($age as $x=>$x_value)
  {
  echo "Key=" . $x . ", Value=" . $x_value;
  echo "<br>";
  }
?>
